Members of the South African Communist Party are picketing outside the NPA offices in Pretoria. They are calling for further investigations and action against those implicated in state capture. Courtesy of #DSTV403 PRETORIA - A group of SACP members picketed outside of the NPA offices in Pretoria on Friday. Jacob Mamabolo read out the group's memorandum in front of the offices. READ: SACP wants NPA to start prosecuting state capture culprits In a press release, the SACP said the purpose of the picket is to demand investigative and prosecutorial action against those implicated in state capture based on the evidence currently available. 